# HMK Implementation Audit

## Bugs (documented features that silently misbehave)

### Bug 1 — Char-range exclusion is silently ignored

**Spec (lines 46, 59):**

```text
{a..z, !d..f}   // lowercase, excluding d–f
```

**Actual:** `d`, `e`, `f` are matched anyway. Exclusions on `char_range`, `named_alpha`, and `full_alpha` nodes are parsed and stored in `node.metadata["exclusions"]` by phase3, but `_match_semantic` in `engine/_match.py` never reads them for those node types. Exclusions only work on `upper_bound` / `lower_bound` / `bounded_range` (value-range nodes) and `union`.

**Fix:** Thread exclusion checks through `_match_char_range`, `_match_named_alpha`, and `_match_full_alpha`.

---

### ~~Bug 2 — Token-position ranges raise CompileError~~ ✅ Fixed

`{cat..dog}` now resolves to a `string_range` node and matches any string lexicographically between the two endpoints. Equal-length endpoints (the common case) match strings of exactly that length. The spec example comment has been updated to reflect the actual semantic: `{cat..dog} // cat,cau,...,dof,dog`.

---

## Partial / Approximated

### Issue 3 — Grouped-class multi-char tokens flattened

**Spec (line 136):**

```text
{{a,bc},{def,ghi}}   // 2 groups with multi-char tokens
```

**Actual:** `_match_group_class` in `engine/_match.py` builds a flat char set `{a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h,i}` and matches any of those chars in any order, ignoring group membership per position. The common single-char case (`{{a,A},{b,B}}`) works correctly; multi-char tokens within a group do not.

---

### Issue 4 — `hexi` named alphabet is a no-op

`NAMED_ALPHABETS["hexi"] = None` and there is no virtual-alphabet expansion path for `hexi` in `_match_named_alpha`. `{hexi}` matches nothing. The spec table lists `hexi` as the case-insensitive hex alphabet (implied zip of `hex` and `HEX`). Either implement it as a union `{hex,HEX}` at match time or document it as unsupported.

---

### Issue 5 — Virtual alphabets (`ascii`, `uni`) cannot be used as range bounds

**Spec:** `ascii` and `uni` act as α in arithmetic, implying e.g.
`{{ascii}..A}` should work.

**Actual:** Raises uncaught `ValueError` (not `CompileError`) from `_value_bounds`because virtual alphabets have no string value to compute positions against. The error is not user-friendly and the limitation is undocumented.

---

### Issue 6 — Chained `{{.}}` deferred resolution not implemented

**Spec (line 210):**

> `{{.}}` in a chained template is deferred — it resolves to the result of applying the remaining chain to the current match, not the raw text.

**Actual:** Multi-step chains `pattern => template => pattern => template` treat each step independently. `{{.}}` in a middle template renders the raw matched text, not the output of the remainder of the chain. The North Star examples only use two-step chains, so this does not affect current tests.

---

## Docs Issues

### Docs Issue 7 — North Star IPv4 pattern has literal spaces

**Spec (line 242):**

```text
{{dec}..255} {.} {{dec}..255} {.} {{dec}..255} {.} {{dec}..255}
```

**Actual:** HMK is whitespace-significant outside `{...}`. The spaces around `{.}` are literal — this pattern matches `192 . 168 . 1 . 1`, not `192.168.1.1`. The working pattern (used in the north_star tests) is:

```text
{{dec}..255}{.}{{dec}..255}{.}{{dec}..255}{.}{{dec}..255}
```

The spec should either remove the decorative spaces or annotate them as illustrative only.

---

## What Aligns Well

- **τ/α cardinality model** — singleton detection, parse-time evaluation, and bound classification all behave exactly as specified.
- **Repetition by equality** — `{a..z}[3]` requires `aaa`, `bbb`, etc., not any mix; backtracking longest-first works.
- **No-anchor scanning** — no implicit start/end anchors; engine scans left to right and returns all non-overlapping matches, consistent throughout.
- **Named alphabets** (`dec`, `hex`, `HEX`, `b32`, `b58`, `b64`, `b85`) — all correct; exclusions in `b58` (`!I`, `!O`, `!l`) applied at alphabet construction, not at match time.
- **Value-range arithmetic** (`upper_bound`, `lower_bound`, `bounded_range`) — including exclusions on numeric ranges (e.g. `{dec}..255, !128..191`).
- **Padding** (`{N: expr}`, `{: expr}`) — fixed and variable-width both work.
- **Captures** — 0-based left-to-right numbering, dot-notation sub-captures, `{{#N}}` count references all correct.
- **Separators** (`<<sep>>`) — lazy span, split semantics, `<<\n>>` on full input.
- **Transformers** (`=>`) — two-step chains (the common case) work correctly.
- **Singleton constructors** (`{z}[33]` as τ bound) — cardinality-based classification is implemented and tested.
